revision.text:
{{Infobox journal | title = Administrative Science Quarterly | cover = [[File:AdministrativeScienceQuarterly.jpg|200px]] | caption=Cover page, June 2002 | discipline = [[Management]] | editor = [[Gerald F. Davis]] [[Henrich R. Greve]] - from 1st July 2016 | publisher = [[SAGE Publications]] for the [[Samuel Curtis Johnson Graduate School of Management]], [[Cornell University]] | country = United States | abbreviation = Adm. Sci. Q. | history = 1956–present | frequency = Quarterly | impact = 5.878 | impact-year = 2017 | website = http://www2.johnson.cornell.edu/publications/asq/ | link1 = http://www.sagepub.com/journals/Journal202065 | link1-name = Journal page at publisher website | link2 = http://asq.sagepub.com/content/by/year | link2-name = Online archive | ISSN = 0001-8392 | eISSN = 1930-3815 | JSTOR = 00018392 | LCCN = 57059226 | CODEN = ASCQAG | OCLC = 01461102 }} '''''Administrative Science Quarterly''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering the field of [[organizational studies]]. The journal was established in 1956 and is published by [[SAGE Publications]] for the [[Samuel Curtis Johnson Graduate School of Management]] at [[Cornell University]]. For 2007, it was ranked as the #16 academic journal in business by ''[[Financial Times]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.journal-ranking.com/ranking/web/docs/pdf/business%20top%2040.pdf |title=Financial Times Top Academic Journals in the Business |author= |year=2007 |work= |publisher=[[Financial Times]] |accessdate=16 October 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110819031344/http://journal-ranking.com/ranking/web/docs/pdf/business%20top%2040.pdf |archivedate=August 19, 2011 }}</ref>
== Scope == ''Administration Science Quarterly'' publishes theoretical and empirical papers based on dissertations as well as the work of more established scholars. The interdisciplinary journal also contains work in organizational theory, and informative book reviews.
==Abstracting and indexing== ''Administration Science Quarterly'' is abstracted and indexed in, among other databases: [[SCOPUS]], and the [[Social Sciences Citation Index]]. According to the ''[[Journal Citation Reports]]'', its 2017 [[impact factor]] is 5.878, ranking it 9 out of 209 journals in the category ‘Management’,<ref name=WoS>{{cite book |year=2017 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Management|title=2017 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Social Sciences |work=Web of Science |postscript=.}}</ref> and 11 out of 140 journals in the category ‘Business’.<ref name=WoS1>{{cite book |year=2017 |chapter=Journals Ranked by Impact: Business |title=2017 [[Journal Citation Reports]] |publisher=[[Thomson Reuters]] |edition=Social Sciences |work=Web of Science |postscript=.}}</ref>
