{{Infobox NRHP | name =Building at 419 West Baltimore Street | nrhp_type = | image = 419WestBaltimoreStreet.jpg | caption = 419 West Baltimore Street, August 2011 | location= 419 W. [[Baltimore Street|Baltimore St.]], [[Baltimore, Maryland]] | coordinates = {{coord|39|17|21|N|76|37|20|W|display=inline,title}} | locmapin = United States Baltimore#Maryland#USA | architecture = Federal, Italianate | added = September 30, 1994 | area = less than one acre | governing_body = Private | mpsub = {{NRHP url|id=64500255|title=Cast Iron Architecture of Baltimore MPS}} | refnum = 94001171<ref name="nris">{{NRISref|version=2010a}}</ref> }}
'''Building at 419 West Baltimore Street''', also known as Harry Guss Inc., is a historic [[retail]] and [[wholesale]] building located at [[Baltimore]], [[Maryland]], [[United States]]. It is a three-story gable-roofed [[Flemish bond]] brick [[Federal architecture|Federal]]-style building built about 1840. Around 1875, a four-bay [[cast iron architecture|cast-iron storefront]] was added at street level. It was used in the garment manufacturing and sales industries.<ref name="mht_ihp">{{cite web|url=https://mht.maryland.gov/secure/medusa/PDF/NR_PDFs/NR-1132.pdf |title=National Register of Historic Places Registration: Building at 419 West Baltimore Street|date=May 1990|accessdate=2016-03-01 |author=Peter E. Kurtze|publisher=Maryland Historical Trust}}</ref>
Building at 419 West Baltimore Street was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1994.<ref name="nris"/>
