'''Frédéric Fekkai''' (born 1958) is a [[France|French]] celebrity [[hairstylist]] and entrepreneur in the beauty industry.
==Early life== Fekkai was born and raised in [[Aix-en-Provence]], [[France]]. His father was Algerian and his mother Vietnamese. In 1979 at the age of 21, Fekkai moved to New York to start his career.<ref name=HPVillageJan08>http://www.hpvillage.com/wp-content/uploads/2010/03/Fekkai_January.pdf</ref>
==Career== After creating [[hairstyle]]s for [[model (person)|models]] on both catwalks and magazine covers, he opened two [[Beauty salon|salons]] in New York City and [[Los Angeles, California|Los Angeles]] and went on to launch his own line of hair care products. Fekkai has styled the hair of many prominent women, such as [[Kim Basinger]], [[Jessica Lange]], [[Sigourney Weaver]],<ref>{{cite news| author = [[Bryony Gordon]]| title = A hairstylist stars don't leave home without| publisher = Telegraph Media Group (Online version of [[The Daily Telegraph]])| url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/fashion/main.jhtml?xml=/fashion/2005/06/22/effred22.xml&sSheet=/fashion/2005/06/24/ixfashion.html| date = 2005-06-22| accessdate = 2007-05-02| location=London}}</ref> [[Claudia Schiffer]], [[Debra Messing]], [[Renée Zellweger]],<ref>{{cite web| title = Biography of Frederic Fekkai| publisher = ''New Beauty'' magazine| url = http://www.newbeauty.com/board/fekkai.aspx| accessdate = 2007-05-03 }}</ref> and [[Hillary Clinton]]. He is often regarded as a [[celebrity]] hair stylist.<ref>{{cite web| author =| title = The Stars and Valentino From the show ''Oprah Goes to Paris''| publisher = [[The Oprah Winfrey Show]]| url = http://www.oprah.com/tows/slide/200410/20041020/slide_20041020_115.jhtml| accessdate = 2007-05-03 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news| author = [[Jane Clayson]], on [[The Early Show]]| title = Summer Hair: Naturally Free| publisher = CBS Interactive Inc. (Online version of [[CBS News]])| url = http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2002/06/24/earlyshow/living/beauty/main513194.shtml| date = 2002-06-25| accessdate = 2007-05-03 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news| author = Kate Novack| title = Closet Capers, Three stylish lads share the secrets of their hip haberdashery| publisher = [[Time (magazine)|TIME]] Online Edition| url = http://www.time.com/time/2004/style/090604/article/closet_capers_three_sty12a.html| accessdate = 2007-05-03| date=2004-09-06}}</ref>
In 2015, Fekkai and his wife acquired Côté Bastide, a 25-year-old lifestyle brand from his hometown of Aix-en-Provence. The couple relaunched the business as Bastide, a collection of natural beauty and luxury home products.<ref name="auto">{{cite news| author = [[Peter Born]]| title = Frederic Fekkai Recassts Provence with Bastide| publisher = WWD)| url = http://wwd.com/beauty-industry-news/products/frederic-fekkai-provence-bastide-10716816/| date = 2016-12-02 | accessdate = 2017-01-24| location=New York}}</ref> The name is inspired by the couple's own [[Bastide (Provençal manor)]] in Aix<ref>{{cite news| author = [[FERNANDA EBERSTADT]]| title = Frédéric Fekkai’s Gorgeous Vacation Home in the South of France| publisher = Architectural Digest)| url = http://www.architecturaldigest.com/story/frederic-fekkai-vacation-home-south-france/| date = 2016-02-02 | accessdate = 2017-01-24| location=New York}}</ref>
==Personal life== Fekkai divides his time between New York City and Aix-en-Provence, France<ref name="auto"/>
