{{Infobox person | name = Ulf G. Lindén | image = Ulf_G._Lindén.jpg | alt = | caption = | birth_name = <!-- only use if different from name --> | birth_date = {{Birth date|1937|12|13|df=yes}} | birth_place = | death_date = {{Death date and age|2009|1|3|1937|12|13|df=yes}} | death_place = | nationality = [[Sweden]] | other_names = | occupation = entrepreneur | years_active = | known_for = Lindén group | notable_works = }} '''Ulf Gösta Lindén''' (13 December 1937 &ndash; 3 January 2009) was a [[Sweden|Swedish]] entrepreneur, owner and president of the Lindén group. The Lindén group is the majority owner of Becker.<ref>[http://di.se/Avdelningar/Artikel.aspx?stat=0&ArticleID=2009%5c01%5c14%5c319437&SectionId=Ettan&menusection=Startsidan;Huvudnyheter&o=sp4 Skånes rikaste industriman död], Dagens Industri, January 14, 2009.</ref>
Ulf G. Lindén was the CEO of Swedish chemical group [[Beckers AB|Beckers]] when he was hired by [[Volvo]] in 1979. Then, Volvo was the largest corporation in Sweden. Due to his tough management style, Lindén was nicknamed "[[Pehr G. Gyllenhammar]]'s [[hitman]]",<ref>Pehr G. Gyllenhammar was the President and CEO of Volvo.</ref> especially after his role in turning down Volvo's merger with chemical group [[Fermenta]]. Lindén retired from Volvo in 1987 to focus on the Lindén group.
